724480f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 102nd Street (West)
724480f-a.text:
West End Avenue, east side, from 1OEnd to 1O3rd Streets, showing
860 to 878 West End Avenue. The last three brownstone houses,
on the corner of 103rd Street, will be demolished late in 1922 for
an apartment building.
This is a typical aummer photograph. Compare the winter photograph
of 862-64-66.
Probably June 1911.

724481f.text:

residences built about 1900. Compare this with the summer photo-

Probably late 1910.

724482f.text:
(1)
B63-55-67 West End Avenue, west side, between 102nd and 103rd
Streets, residences built in the mid 1890's. In 1925 the
entire southern half of this block, including these three,
will be demolished for an apartment house.
About 191O.

724478f.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 102nd Street
724478f.text:
854-56 West End Avenue, east side, adjoining S.E. corner of
102nd Street.
These two and the corner house, 858, were the first three houses
to be erected in this block, and date back to the late 1880's.
The adjoining small apartment house, 850-52, was built about
1900.
About 1910.
A closer view, taken simultaneously with the above.
About 1910.

724479f-a.title: Manhattan: West End Avenue - 102nd Street (West)
724479f-a.text:
West End Avenue, west side, at 10End Street, showing the new 865
West End Avenue apartment house nearing completion. It replaces
five old houses, three of which are shown in photographs about
191O.
The building shown in part on the S.W. corner ts The Standoche,
typical of the earier type of apartment house on this avenue.
1925.
American Photo Service, Inc.
